==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*regna-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[regan]] (Dutch [[regen]]), Old High German [[regan]] (German [[Regen]]), Old Norse ''regn'' (Swedish ''regn''), Gothic [[𐍂𐌹𐌲𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /rejn/

===Noun===
'''regn''' ''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Old English strong declension|strong]] m''
